  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user\r\nI want to be protected against an attacker sending multiple large files\r\nSo that I won't be consuming too much bandwith\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently we only rate limit data based on the number of packets, but an attacker could potentially send a lower amount of packets so that it does not breach the limit, each one of a large size, which would result in an excessive data consumption.\r\n\r\n### Technical details\r\n\r\nThis will only be a bland mitigation, as currently how to prevent spam is an open question.\r\nWe already have limits in place for the number of messages, this can be easily extended to check for packet size.",
